     "The GRIP domain - a novel Golgi-targeting domain found in several
     coiled-coil proteins."
     Curr. Biol. 9:377-380(1999).
     PubMed=10209120
[ 2] Jackson C.L.
     "Membrane traffic: Arl GTPases get a GRIP on the Golgi."
     Curr. Biol. 13:R174-R176(2003).
     PubMed=12620205
[ 3] Panic B., Whyte J.R., Munro S.
     "The ARF-like GTPases Arl1p and Arl3p act in a pathway that interacts
